net.sf.jagg

Class TwoPropAggregator

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.sf.jagg.Aggregator
      • net.sf.jagg.TwoPropAggregator
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    AbstractCovarianceAggregator, CorrelationAggregator, LinearRegressionAggregator, PercentileAggregator

    public abstract class TwoPropAggregator
extends Aggregator
    This abstract class allows for the state necessary to implement aggregate functions over two variables (properties). The aggregation algorithm is the same as in Aggregator, but TwoPropAggregators have access to two property names. An example of a TwoPropAggregators is a CovarianceAggregator, which compares samples of two variables to determine the covariance.
    Since:
    0.1.0
    Author:
    Randy Gettman

      • setProperty

        protected void setProperty(String property)
        Sets both property Strings. Subclasses may override this method if they want to extract more information from the property string, e.g. "Name(property, property2, addlInfo)". The default implementation expects two property names separated by a comma.
        Overrides:
        setProperty in class Aggregator
        Parameters:
        property - The property string, with at least one comma separating two actual property names.
